  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-pea-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-pea-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>portobello mushroom tortelloni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>tortelloni</strong> for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>tortelloni</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-pea-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-pea-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine <strong>half </strong>your<strong> grated Italian hard</strong> <strong>cheese</strong> (save the rest for later!) with your <strong>cornflour </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Gradually add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [300ml] </span><strong>milk</strong> and mix until fully combined – this is your <strong>creamy sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-pea-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the bacon lardons are golden, add the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-pea-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, reduce the heat to medium-high, then add your<strong> creamy sauce</strong> and <strong>blanched peas</strong> to the pan, give everything a good mix up and bring to the boil</p><p>Cook for 30 secs, or until the sauce has slightly thickened, then add your <strong>drained tortelloni </strong>to the pan with a splash of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and cook for a final 30 secs or until the sauce is coating the pasta – this is your <strong>creamy bacon & pea sauce with mushroom tortelloni</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-pea-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy bacon & pea sauce with mushroom tortelloni</strong> topped with the<strong> remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and <strong>chopped basil</strong></p><p>Drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
